-- EBRD, Splitska Banka Lend 75 Million Euros to Local Companies
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-12-04T14:38:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-04/ebrd-splitska-banka-lend-75-million-euros-to-local-companies.html
Splitska Banka d.d. , the Croatian
unit of  Societe Generale SA (GLE) , and the  European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development , will lend 75 million euros ($98
million) to private businesses and individual consumers in
 Croatia .  The funds will be used with a “particular focus” on
increasing lending to small and medium-sized businesses, as well
as on improving regional expansion and increasing
competitiveness, the EBRD said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  